> You're a key ingredient in the fight against AIDS. To that end, HelloFresh has teamed up
> with chef Carla Hall to bring you her Summery Lemon Chicken recipe, which was specially
> crafted for EAT (RED) SAVE LIVES.

Wash and dry all produce. Remove stems and large ribs from @Tuscan kale{4%ounce} and discard.
Chop leaves into bite-sized pieces. Zest @lemon{1} until you have 1 tsp zest, then cut into
halves. Add kale, zest, and juice from one lemon half to a #medium bowl{}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Massage leaves with hands until tender, then set aside.

Bring @water{1%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1} and a pinch of salt to a boil in a small
#pot{}. Pick @tarragon{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; discard stems. Roughly chop leaves.
Mince @garlic{1%clove}.

Halve @heirloom grape tomatoes{4%ounce} lengthwise. Cut @lemon{1} into wedges.

Once stock is boiling, add @couscous{1/2%cup} to pot. Remove from heat, cover, and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{5%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat
@chicken breasts{12%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}, then season all over with salt and
pepper. Add to pan and cook until browned on surface and no longer pink in center,
~chicken{6-10%minutes} per side. Remove from heat and let rest ~{5%minutes}.

While chicken cooks, make the dressing: in a #small bowl{}, whisk together @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon},
@brown sugar{1%tablespoon}, @tarragon{1%tsp}, juice from remaining lemon half,
@olive oil{4%tablespoon}, and salt and pepper (to taste).

In another small bowl, make the chimichurri: combine remaining tarragon, garlic,
@chili flakes{1%teaspoon}(to taste), a squeeze of lemon, and a large drizzle of olive oil.
Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}, then season with lemon juice, salt, and pepper to taste.

Toss kale in #bowl{} with tomatoes and 1 tablespoon dressing. Divide couscous, kale mixture,
and chicken between plates. Spoon over remaining dressing. Serve with chimichurri for
dipping and lemon wedges on the side.